                                                                                                                       7                                      DareDevils spend fortune on Delhi duo
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The Delhi DareDevilss decision to send two of their injured players  Gautam Gambhir and Ashish Nehra  to Sri Lanka for treatment is costing the team management more than Rs 40 lakh.         
	Its costing us a fortune, said a source in the DareDevils team. The two players have been sent on a chartered flight to Colombo. They will be back on the same flight The bill for the special flight alone is Rs 40 lakh, added the source.         
	Gambhir suffered a hamstring injury in the match against the Mumbai Indians while Nehra had a rib injury before the start of the IPL. Both have been sent to Sri Lanka to consult an ayurvedic doctor, who is believed to have a huge reputation.         
	Our Sri Lankan recruit, Dilshan Tillekaratne, convinced the team management about consulting this particular doctor, said the source.         
	He also spoke to a top Sri Lanka politician to fix an immediate appointment for the two players.         
	Both the players are expected to back before the DareDevils away match against the Royal Challengers Bangalore on Thursday.                                                                                                                     
